<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36068a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36068a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36068a"> 68(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Under the blade bone of / a whale / You may find good beer / and ale; / He in sea was sent to / swim, / So froth your pots up / to the brim.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Adjoining Felster&apos;s house on the east side (now portion of the Abbey Theatre), stood a well-frequented beerhouse and taproom, &hellip;. Over the entrance door was the following inscription on a large bone of some animal purporting to be that of a whale:&mdash; <br>&ldquo;Under the blade bone of a whale <br>You may find good beer and ale; <br>He in sea was sent to swim, <br>So froth your pots up to be brim.&rdquo; <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
